/code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/asinh\"><code>Math.asinh()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/atan\"><code>Math.atan()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/atan2\"><code>Math.atan2()</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/atanh\"><code>Math.atanh()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/cbrt\"><code>Math.cbrt()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/ceil\"><code>Math.ceil()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/clz32\"><code>Math.clz32()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/cos\"><code>Math.cos()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/cosh\"><code>Math.cosh()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/exp\"><code>Math.exp()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/expm1\"><code>Math.expm1()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/floor\"><code>Math.floor()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/fround\"><code>Math.fround()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/hypot\"><code>Math.hypot()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/imul\"><code>Math.imul()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/log\"><code>Math.log()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/log10\"><code>Math.log10()</code></a></li><li><em><code>Math.log1p()</code></em></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/log2\"><code>Math.log2()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/max\"><code>Math.max()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/min\"><code>Math.min()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/pow\"><code>Math.pow()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/random\"><code>Math.random()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/round\"><code>Math.round()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/sign\"><code>Math.sign()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/sin\"><code>Math.sin()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/sinh\"><code>Math.sinh()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/sqrt\"><code>Math.sqrt()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/tan\"><code>Math.tan()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/tanh\"><code>Math.tanh()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/trunc\"><code>Math.trunc()</code></a></li></ol></li><li><strong>Vererbung:</strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object\"><code>Object</code></a></strong></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Eigenschaften</strong></a><ol><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/constructor\"><code>Object.prototype.constructor</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/proto\"><code>Object.prototype.__proto__</code></a></li></ol></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Methoden</strong></a><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/hasOwnProperty\"><code>Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty()</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/isPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/propertyIsEnumerable\"><code>Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/setPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.setPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toLocaleString\"><code>Object.prototype.toLocaleString()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/valueOf\"><code>Object.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect1\"></div>\n\n<p>Die <strong><code>Math.log1p()</code></strong> Funktion gibt den natürlichen Logarithmus (Logarithmus zur Basis <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/E\"><code>e</code></a>) von 1 + x zurück. Das bedeutet</p>\n\n<p><math display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mo>∀</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mstyle mathvariant=\"monospace\"><mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"thinmathspace\">Math.log1p</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mstyle><mo>=</mo><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">ln</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"TeX\">\\forall x &gt; -1, \\mathtt{\\operatorname{Math.log1p}(x)} = \\ln(1 + x)</annotation></semantics></math></p>\n\n<div id=\"sect2\"><iframe class=\"interactive\" height=\"490\" src=\"https://interactive-examples.mdn.mozilla.net/pages/js/math-log1p.html\" title=\"MDN Web Docs Interactive Example\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"syntaxbox notranslate\"><code>Math.log1p(<var>x</var>)</code></pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameter","title":"Parameter","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"x\"><code>x</code></dt>\n <dd>Eine Zahl.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"rückgabewert","title":"Rückgabewert","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Den natürliche Logarithmus (zur Basis <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/E\"><code>e</code></a>) von 1 plus der gegebenen Zahl. Wenn die Zahl kleiner als <strong>-1</strong> ist, wird <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a> zurückgegeben.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"beschreibung","title":"Beschreibung","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Für sehr kleine Zahlen für <code>x</code> kann das Addieren mit 1 zu verlusten in der Präzision führen. Die Zahlen in JavaScript haben eine Genauigkeit von 15 Stellen. <code> 1 + 1e-15 =&nbsp;1.000000000000001</code>, aber <code>1 + 1e-16 =&nbsp;1.000000000000000</code> und damit exakt <code>1</code><code>.0</code> in dieser Arithmetik, weil Ziffern nach der 15 Stelle gerundet werden.</p>\n\n<p>Wenn <code>log(1 + x)</code> berechnet wird, bekommt man ein Ergebnis sehr na an <code>x</code>, wenn <code>x</code> klein ist (das ist der Grund, warum es 'natürlicher' Logarithmus heißt). Wenn <code>Math.log(1 + 1.1111111111e-15)</code> berechnet wird sollte man ein Ergebnis nah an <code>1.1111111111e-15</code> bekommt. Stattdessen berechnet man den Logarithmus von <code><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">1.00000000000000111022</span></code><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> (die Rundung geschieht im Binärsystem und ist manchmal unschön) un erhält das Ergebnis <code>1.11022...e-15</code> mit nur 3 korrekten Stellen. Wenn stattdessen <code>Math.log1p(</code></span><code>1.1111111111e-15</code><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><code>)</code> berechnet wird, bekommt man ein besseres Ergebnis von <code>1.1111111110999995e-15</code> mit 15 korrekten Stellen in der Präzision (aktuell 16 in diesem Fall).</span></p>\n\n<p>Wenn der Wert von <code>x</code> kleiner als -1 ist, gibt die Funktion immer den Wert <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a> zurück.</p>\n\n<p>Weil <code>log1p()</code> eine statische Funktion von <code>Math</code> ist, wird es immer als <code>Math.log1p()</code> eingesetzt<code>,</code> jedoch nicht als Methode eines erzeugten <code>Math</code> Objektes (<code>Math</code> ist kein Konstruktor).</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"beispiele","title":"Beispiele","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"einsatz_von_math.log1p()","title":"Einsatz von <code>Math.log1p()</code>","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log1p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">// 0.6931471805599453</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log1p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">// 0</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log1p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// -Infinity</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log1p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// NaN</span>\n</code></pre></div>","titleAsText":"Einsatz von Math.log1p()"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"polyfill","title":"Polyfill","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Diese Funktion kann folgendermaßen emuliert werden:</p>\n\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>log1p <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>log1p <span class=\"token operator\">||</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">x</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> x<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"spezifikationen","title":"Spezifikationen","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Spezifikation</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Kommentar</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/#sec-math.log1p\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 2015 (6th Edition, ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Math.log1p' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>Initiale Definition.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-math.log1p\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Math.log1p' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-living\">Lebender Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browserkompatibilität","isH3":false,"query":"javascript.builtins.Math.log1p","dataURL":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/log1p/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"siehe_auch","title":"Siehe auch","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/exp\"><code>Math.exp()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/log\"><code>Math.log()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/log10\"><code>Math.log10()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/log2\"><code>Math.log2()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/pow\"><code>Math.pow()</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Beschreibung","id":"beschreibung"},{"text":"Beispiele","id":"beispiele"},{"text":"Polyfill","id":"polyfill"},{"text":"Spezifikationen","id":"spezifikationen"},{"text":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browserkompatibilität"},{"text":"Siehe auch","id":"siehe_auch"}],"summary":"Die Math.log1p() Funktion gibt den natürlichen Logarithmus (Logarithmus zur Basis e) von 1 + x zurück. Das bedeutet","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Math.log1p()","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Math.log1p()","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Math.log1p()","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Math.log1p()","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"Math.log1p()","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Math.log1p()","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"de/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/math/log1p","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/de/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/math/log1p/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/de/docs/Web","title":"Webtechnologien für Entwickler"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript","title":"JavaScript"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference","title":"JavaScript-Referenz"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects","title":"Globale Objekte"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math","title":"Math"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/log1p","title":"Math.log1p()"}],"pageTitle":"Math.log1p() - JavaScript | MDN","noIndexing":false}}